results.name: a(n) gives sum of number of common unitary divisors of n and m, where m runs from 1 to n.
link: Amiram Eldar, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
mathematica: udiv[n_] := Select[Divisors[n], GCD[#, n/#]==1 &]; a[n_] := Module[{d = udiv[n]}, Sum[Length[Intersection[d, udiv[k]]], {k,1,n}]]; Array[a, 100] (* _Amiram Eldar_, Aug 10 2019 *)
program: (PARI) a(n) = {sdivn = Set(); fordiv(n, d, if (gcd(d, n/d) == 1, sdivn = setunion(sdivn, Set(d)))); s = 0; for (m=1, n, sdivm = Set(); fordiv(m, d, if (gcd(d, m/d) == 1, sdivm = setunion(sdivm, Set(d)))); s += length(setintersect(sdivn, sdivm));); return (s);} \\ _Michel Marcus_, Jul 15 2013
